1
00:00:01,950 --> 00:00:05,220
Instructor: We have added ApplicationUser in our models

2
00:00:05,220 --> 00:00:08,460
and we have pushed that to our database,

3
00:00:08,460 --> 00:00:13,323
but the default identity here is still using IdentityUser.

4
00:00:14,340 --> 00:00:17,100
With that, let me run the application

5
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:20,490
and try to see how the default registration

6
00:00:20,490 --> 00:00:22,863
and login functionalities work.

7
00:00:25,080 --> 00:00:28,230
So let me register for a user here

8
00:00:28,230 --> 00:00:32,369
and I will call that test@gmail.com.

9
00:00:32,369 --> 00:00:37,370
Password, I will do Admin123* with a capital A,

10
00:00:37,530 --> 00:00:40,710
because if I only use 123,

11
00:00:40,710 --> 00:00:43,440
you can see password is not strong enough,

12
00:00:43,440 --> 00:00:46,560
so we have to keep something strong.

13
00:00:46,560 --> 00:00:50,493
I will add Admin123* and register.

14
00:00:51,690 --> 00:00:53,730
Perfect, once I register here,

15
00:00:53,730 --> 00:00:56,760
it automatically signs me in.

16
00:00:56,760 --> 00:00:58,770
But if we log out here,

17
00:00:58,770 --> 00:01:02,520
and then if we go to log in, we can try that again.

18
00:01:02,520 --> 00:01:07,230
Test@gmail.com and Admin123.

19
00:01:07,230 --> 00:01:09,540
I did not add the asterisk at the end,

20
00:01:09,540 --> 00:01:12,420
so we should say invalid login attempt.

21
00:01:12,420 --> 00:01:14,100
That looks good.

22
00:01:14,100 --> 00:01:16,473
Now let me type the correct password.

23
00:01:18,060 --> 00:01:21,360
Perfect, with correct password, it logs me in,

24
00:01:21,360 --> 00:01:23,490
and we have a profile,

25
00:01:23,490 --> 00:01:25,050
and on the top right here,

26
00:01:25,050 --> 00:01:28,053
we see Hello test@gmail.com.

27
00:01:29,130 --> 00:01:32,700
Now if you click there, it displays the profile

28
00:01:32,700 --> 00:01:36,090
where it displays username, phone number,

29
00:01:36,090 --> 00:01:39,600
they can update their email, verify email,

30
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:44,310
modify their password, add a two-factor authentication,

31
00:01:44,310 --> 00:01:47,523
and they can download or delete their personal data.

32
00:01:48,360 --> 00:01:51,270
All of this is provided by default

33
00:01:51,270 --> 00:01:54,420
with the identity that we scaffolded.

34
00:01:54,420 --> 00:01:56,490
So you can see when we scaffold,

35
00:01:56,490 --> 00:01:58,590
it provides many things,

36
00:01:58,590 --> 00:02:01,410
not just the basic identity setup,

37
00:02:01,410 --> 00:02:05,640
and it is more like a complete identity package.

38
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:08,789
But of course, if you add more fields to register,

39
00:02:08,789 --> 00:02:12,873
you can always update profile and all the other pages.

40
00:02:13,980 --> 00:02:17,940
But before anything, let me switch back to SQL Server

41
00:02:17,940 --> 00:02:21,060
and examine the user that got created

42
00:02:21,060 --> 00:02:23,703
in the ASP.NET User Stable.

43
00:02:25,050 --> 00:02:27,870
Perfect, you can see we have the record here.

44
00:02:27,870 --> 00:02:29,580
If you scroll to the right,

45
00:02:29,580 --> 00:02:32,730
what should be the Discriminator column?

46
00:02:32,730 --> 00:02:36,603
Will it be ApplicationUser or will it be IdentityUser?

47
00:02:38,040 --> 00:02:42,120
If you said IdentityUser, you are correct,

48
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:44,580
you can see that right here.

49
00:02:44,580 --> 00:02:46,530
Because right now in our application,

50
00:02:46,530 --> 00:02:49,920
the default identity is IdentityUser,

51
00:02:49,920 --> 00:02:52,260
but on top of that, the important thing is,

52
00:02:52,260 --> 00:02:54,570
when we are registering the user,

53
00:02:54,570 --> 00:02:57,330
we are creating an IdentityUser

54
00:02:57,330 --> 00:02:59,463
and not an ApplicationUser.

55
00:03:00,510 --> 00:03:04,440
So we need to modify that, because with IdentityUser,

56
00:03:04,440 --> 00:03:07,830
we will not get city, name, postal code,

57
00:03:07,830 --> 00:03:09,783
state, and street address.

58
00:03:10,650 --> 00:03:13,380
If we want to capture those properties,

59
00:03:13,380 --> 00:03:17,193
we need to find out a way to register an ApplicationUser.

60
00:03:18,772 --> 00:03:22,023
So let me work on that in the next video.

